-- Nifco May Invest $11.9 Million to Build Factory in China, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2010-09-28T19:19:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/nifco-may-invest-11-9-million-to-build-factory-in-china-nikkei-reports.html
Nifco Inc. may invest about 1
billion yen ($11.9 million) to build a factory in China’s Hubei
Province, Nikkei English News reported, without saying how it
obtained the information.  The plant would be Nifco’s sixth in China, Nikkei reported.
Operations are scheduled to start in mid-2011, Nikkei reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  